---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Billing"
  description="Cash-pay billing for behavioral health — invoices per session, payment links by text or email, autopay through Stripe, different rates for different clinicians, and a clear view of who owes what."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Billing"
    title="Get paid faster, <em>with cleaner records.</em>"
    lede="Send an invoice in a click. Let clients pay by tapping a link in a text. Set autopay once and stop chasing. Charge the right rate for the right clinician without keeping a spreadsheet on the side of the monitor. Built for cash-pay and out-of-network practices."
  >
    <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request access</a>
    <a href="/pricing" class="btn btn-secondary">See pricing</a>
  </PageHeader>

  <section class="capabilities">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
        <h2>The work of getting paid, in one place.</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Invoices the way the practice actually invoices</h4>
          <p>Per session, per period, or in batches. Clinicians invoice their own self-pay clients; practice admins can invoice across the whole practice. Voiding an invoice is an admin decision, not a clinician one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Payment links the client can tap</h4>
          <p>Every invoice and every session can generate a secure payment link, sent by email or text. Clients pay in seconds, on their phone, without logging into anything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Autopay, set once</h4>
          <p>A client saves their card; Praxnote charges it after each session. The charge runs in the background — you and your client never wait on a spinning wheel — and if a card fails, the system tells you, not the client mid-checkout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Different rates for different clinicians</h4>
          <p>Set a default rate for the practice and override it per clinician when their license, experience, or contract calls for a different number. The right rate applies to the right session, every time. The spreadsheet on the side of the monitor can go.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>A clear view of who owes what</h4>
          <p>See outstanding balances at a glance — across the whole practice, by clinician, or by client. Sort by how long a balance has been outstanding. Send a payment-link nudge, set up autopay, or export the list for your accountant.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Attendance and AI use, on the same dashboard</h4>
          <p>See utilization by clinician and AI draft usage by clinician or by skill, alongside the billing numbers. The reports your monthly admin meeting actually asks for, ready when you sit down.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="role-matrix alt">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who can do what</p>
        <h2>The right hands on the right work.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Billing is sensitive. Praxnote enforces who can do what at the server, not just in the
          interface — so the rules can't be worked around. The picture below is what gets recorded
          in the activity history every time.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="table-scroll">
      <table class="table-clean role-matrix-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Role</th>
            <th>Create invoice</th>
            <th>Send invoice</th>
            <th>Void invoice</th>
            <th>View invoices</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Clinician</strong></td>
            <td>Their own self-pay clients</td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>No</td>
            <td>Their own clients</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Practice admin</strong></td>
            <td>Anyone in the practice</td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Practice-wide</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pluggable">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Honest about the niche</p>
        <h2>Built first for cash-pay and out-of-network.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Praxnote's billing is excellent for the practice that doesn't depend on insurance — cash-pay,
          out-of-network, sliding-scale. We're honest about what it does not yet do: in-network claims,
          ERA posting, eligibility checks, denial management, prior authorizations. Those are on the
          long-term roadmap; they aren't in the product today. If your practice depends on them,
          Praxnote isn't the right choice yet.
        </p>
      </header>

      <ul class="checks">
        <li>Stripe handles the card processing at Stripe's rates — Praxnote adds nothing</li>
        <li>Practices that handle payments outside the platform can still track invoices inside it</li>
        <li>Superbills generate cleanly for clients who want to submit their own claims to insurance</li>
        <li>Sliding-scale and pro-bono sessions are handled directly, not as workarounds</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    eyebrow="See it on a real session"
    heading="From a session to a paid invoice in five minutes."
    body="On a walk-through we'll generate an invoice from a real (or sample) session, send a payment link, set up autopay, and look at the outstanding-balance view. Most practices say billing is the reason they migrated."
    primaryHref="/demo"
    primaryLabel="Book a walk-through"
    secondaryHref="/solutions/practice-admins"
    secondaryLabel="More for practice admins"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .capabilities { padding: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .alt { background: var(--paper-warm); border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
  .pluggable { padding: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0; }
  .section-head { max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .section-head .lede { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .role-matrix-table th:not(:first-child), .role-matrix-table td:not(:first-child) { text-align: center; }
  .table-scroll { overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
  .table-scroll table { min-width: 640px; }
  .card h4 { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .card p { color: var(--stone-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.65; }
</style>
